{
    "title": "Hierarchical Structure",
    "category": "Documentation",
    "template": "base.html",
    "style": "text_style",
    "content": [
        {
            "type": "title",
            "text": "Nesting & Recursive Blocks"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Atlas engine is built on a recursive rendering logic. A <code>blocks</code> element can contain an array of other <code>blocks</code>, allowing you to create deeply nested documentation hierarchies."
        },
        {
            "type": "blocks",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "id": "smart_headings",
                    "title": "1. Smart Heading Logic",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "To maintain semantic structure without manual tagging, use <code>type: 'title'</code>. The engine automatically calculates the correct heading level (h2 through h6) based on the nesting depth."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "blocks",
                            "blocks": [
                                {
                                    "id": "nesting_example",
                                    "title": "Example: This is an H3",
                                    "content": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "text",
                                            "text": "Because this block is inside another block, its title automatically shrank from H2 to H3."
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "visibility_depth",
                    "title": "2. Automatic Visibility Depth",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "To prevent 'Information Overload', the engine implements a default visibility rule: <b>The 2-Level Rule</b>."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "list",
                            "items": [
                                "<b>Levels 1 & 2:</b> Expanded by default (depth 2 and 3).",
                                "<b>Levels 3+:</b> Automatically collapsed on page load (depth 4+)."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "note",
                            "variant": "warning",
                            "text": "Any block at Level 3 or deeper will appear with the <code>is-collapsed</code> state unless you manually override it."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "manual_overrides",
                    "title": "3. Manual Toggles",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "You can bypass the automatic visibility logic by using the <code>collapsed</code> property in the JSON."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "list",
                            "items": [
                                "<code>'collapsed': true</code> — Forces a block to start hidden.",
                                "<code>'collapsed': false</code> — Forces a deep block to start visible."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}